OL,7,FThe law campaigners have long called
OL,8,Ffor a legal duty of candour on public
OL,9,Fauthorities and officials to tell the
OL,10,Ftruth and proactively co-operate with
OL,11,Fofficial investigations and inquiries.
OL,13,FThis would include the potential for
OL,14,Fcriminal sanctions for officials or
OL,15,Forganisations which mislead or
OL,16,Fobstruct investigations.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/10
